    "Victoria's compact size is part of the story.\n",
    "A modest number of route-kilometres, placed well,\n",
    "can cover a substantial share of the city.\n",
    "That's not a caveat — the political will to build here was real,\n",
    "and hard-won.\n",
    "But it does mean the challenge scales differently for bigger cities.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "### 🥯 Montreal: real gains, real network\n",
    "\n",
    "Montreal has the largest absolute high-comfort network of the three cities.\n",
    "And it kept growing.\n",
    "\n",
    "Between 2019 and 2024, population-weighted access rose from\n",
    "**[X]% to [Y]%**.\n",
    "In raw kilometres, Montreal's gains dwarf Victoria's.\n",
    "\n",
    "Central to this: the **REV** — Réseau Express Vélo.\n",
    "A set of high-frequency protected lanes built explicitly as\n",
    "cycling rapid transit, not recreational paths. That framing matters."
